    <node id="1. Qualifications Wales is the regulator of awarding bodies in Wales, focusing on regulating the design and delivery of qualifications and assessments. Their role does not include regulating commercial publishers or the provision of textbooks.&#10;2. They ensure that teachers and pupils are prepared for examinations by setting out approval criteria for the specifications of qualifications and sample assessment materials. This helps teachers understand what is expected of them and their pupils in the examinations.&#10;3. During the design of qualifications, Qualifications Wales forms groups to discuss available resources and identify who would be best placed to fill gaps in resources.&#10;4. They maintain standards by ensuring that awards of qualifications are fair through monitoring awarding processes and setting out methods for awarding grades. Comparable outcomes are used to ensure that the same grade is awarded from one year to the next, considering possible performance differences due to various factors like resources.&#10;5. While technically possible, comparing teacher assessments and expected grades to actual grade outcomes on a sample basis may not provide highly reliable evidence due to historical low correlation between predicted and achieved grades. Creating more sample assessments could also increase the risk of teaching to the test." />
