se learning experiences that do not solely focus on test-taking strategies or content.&#10;&#10;In summary, while creating more sample assessments can provide valuable practice materials for students, it also poses risks related to teaching to the test and may inadvertently narrow the curriculum's scope. By carefully considering the production timeline of curriculum resources like textbooks and diversifying available learning materials, future reforms can help mitigate these issues and promote a more balanced approach to education.">
