e many resources available digitally in both languages at the same time. Teachers should be made aware of these resources to reduce the need for independent translations and duplication of efforts.&#10;&#10;4. Balancing Act between Languages: The vision for teaching in Welsh-medium classes should aim to enrich the learning experience by taking advantage of both the Welsh language and English resources. This can help create a more comprehensive and balanced educational environment.&#10;&#10;5. Addressing the Root Cause of Translation Needs: It is essential to understand what causes the need for translations in order to address the issue effectively. By identifying the source of the problem, stakeholders can work together to find solutions that benefit both learners and teachers.">
