ntly. Additionally, digital learning environments support diverse learning styles, allowing students to engage with content through multimedia formats that suit their individual needs.&#10;&#10;However, while digital resources can help bridge gaps in access to supportive materials, they also pose risks related to teaching to the test and narrowing the curriculum's scope. Careful consideration should be given to the production timeline of curriculum resources like textbooks and diversifying available learning materials to promote a more balanced approach to education.&#10;&#10;In summary, addressing the fundamental unfairness in the current education system requires improving digital accessibility and literacy, as well as carefully considering the design and distribution of supportive materials to ensure equal opportunities for all students, regardless of their subject or language of study.">
