    <edge source="1. The WJEC (Welsh Joint Education Committee) and publishers such as Hodder and Illuminate have agreed to produce Welsh-medium textbooks first and then translate them into English. This is to ensure that the Welsh version is available at the same time as the English version.&#10;2. Translation and editing of the Welsh version will be done simultaneously as the textbook is being written, with the understanding that any changes made after approval could cause delays. The publishers have agreed to hold back the English version until the Welsh version is available for simultaneous release.&#10;3. This new approach is being implemented as an experiment at the request of the Welsh Government, and will only apply to textbooks that are currently in development, not those that are already late.&#10;4. The risk of delays due to author edits during the translation process is being mitigated by approving chapters as they are completed, reducing the likelihood of major changes later on.&#10;5. Additionally, an eight-week period has been agreed upon for translation and editing of the Welsh version, ensuring that both versions will be available simultaneously. Draft versions of the English textbook may be made available earlier, but final publication will be held until the Welsh version is complete." target=" textbook?&#10;Speaker: Mike Ebbsworth&#10;Content: We can only work on those books that are in the process of being developed. Naturally, if something is late in English, then that timetable would be affected in terms of a decision that will ultimately have to be taken. But that's the hope: that when new textbooks are produced in English and authored in English, we would look at that eight-week period as a turnaround.&#10;Speaker: Darren Millar AM&#10;Content: I understand the point that you made earlier about the chapter-by-chapter approach, which seems much more equitable. But to suggest that you will delay books that could be available for students and could be available for teachers to be able to access by two months because you haven't got the systems in place to be able to produce them on the same day, seems to be wholly inappropriate. Can I ask, also, why on earth it isn't possible to produce Welsh-medium textbooks first and then translate them to English on occasions?&#10;Speaker: Mike Ebbsworth&#10;Content: We're entirely open to that and to that sort of model.&#10;Speaker: Darren Millar AM&#10;Content: So, why has that never ever been done?&#10;Speaker">
