focused resources that encourage students to analyze, synthesize information, and develop discursive argument skills, moving away from textbook-based learning models. The WJEC, a Welsh examination board, plays a significant role in this process by leveraging its expertise in GCSE and A-level materials to contribute to resources for lower levels, ensuring continuity in the learning experience and better preparing students for the transition to tertiary education.">
