rts. A new approach involves prioritizing Welsh versions first, then translating them into English when possible, starting with textbooks currently in development.&#10;4. Both Darren Millar AM and Mike Ebbsworth recognize the need for improving the availability of both Welsh-medium and English language resources, emphasizing textbooks as fundamental learning resources, especially during exam periods.&#10;5. WJEC has proposed rethinking the subsidy model to support producing resources in two languages for the Welsh curriculum instead of just providing a subsidy for Welsh-medium versions. They are open to contributing more funding to this new approach.&#10;6. There is an ongoing discussion about the length of time it takes to translate resources and what an acceptable waiting period would be. The goal is to reduce delays, with WJEC succeeding in agreeing on an eight-week turnaround for translating Welsh versions of textbooks in development.">
