e of the progression to HE and develop materials emphasizing an analysis-based learning approach, keeping in mind the needs of learners transitioning to higher education. Additionally, HE professionals collaborate to create curriculum-focused resources that encourage students to analyze, synthesize information, and develop discursive argument skills, moving away from textbook-based learning models. The WJEC, a Welsh examination board, plays a significant role in this process by leveraging its expertise in GCSE and A-level materials to contribute to resources for lower levels, ensuring continuity in the learning experience and better preparing students for the transition to tertiary education.">
