    <edge source="1. The Welsh Government has asked publisher Hodder Education, along with other publishers, to delay the English version of certain textbooks as an experiment to ensure equity in the release of new textbooks in both Welsh and English languages. This decision is in response to concerns about different timetables for the availability of learning materials in different languages.&#10;2. Hodder Education and other publishers have agreed to this request, but it only applies to textbooks currently in development and not those that are already late. The eight-week period for translation and editing is intended for new textbooks moving forward.&#10;3. Hodder Education is open to the idea of producing Welsh-medium textbooks first and then translating them into English, which is a new approach being implemented as an experiment at the request of the Welsh Government. However, they can only work on those books that are in the process of being developed.&#10;4. Hodder Education acknowledges the concern about delaying English versions of textbooks by two months but emphasizes the importance of equitable treatment for both languages. They are open to a chapter-by-chapter approach to mitigate this issue." target="1. To ensure that Welsh-medium textbooks are available simultaneously with their English counterparts, the WJEC and publishers like Hodder and Illuminate have agreed to produce the Welsh versions first and then translate them into English. The translation and editing process will happen concurrently as the textbook is written, with an eight-week period set aside for this purpose. Changes made after approval may cause delays, so chapters will be approved as they are completed to reduce the likelihood of major changes later on.&#10;2. A risk mitigation measure being implemented is the approval of chapters as they are completed, reducing the likelihood of major changes later on that could cause delays. The eight-week period for translation and editing aims to ensure that both versions will be available simultaneously, with draft versions of the English textbook possibly made available earlier. However, final publication of both versions will be held until the Welsh version is complete.&#10;3. This approach only applies to new textbooks currently in development, as the focus is on ensuring equity in the release of new textbooks moving forward. If an English version of a textbook is already late in development, the agreed-upon eight-week period for translation and editing may not apply. Producing Welsh-medium textbooks first and then translating them into English is a new approach being implemented as an experiment at the request of the Welsh Government.">
